HEADWORD: Shapely
<hw>Shape"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Shapelier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Shapeliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Well-formed; having
a regular shape; comely; symmetrical.</def> <rj><au>T.
Warton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Waste sandy valleys, once perplexed with thorn,⟦br⟧
The spiry fir and <qex>shapely</qex> box adorn.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where the <qex>shapely</qex> column stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Couper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fit; suitable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Shaply</qex> for to be an alderman.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shaper</ent>⟦br⟧
